events.name: GDG Savannah Meetup
events.description: This is the inaugural GDG Savannah meetup. We'll use this time to kick off a regular occurrence of GDG Savannah meetup events happening at least once per quarter. During this first meetup, we'll discuss planning and organization, along with some of the national GDG content offerings and we'll perform a formal brainstorming session to share ideas and explore potential future meetup topics.
events.how_to_find_us: Enter 2222 Bull St and proceed up the stairs. Turn right into the hallway and follow until a large opening into the main room on the right.

events.name: GDG Savannah Fall Meetup
events.description:
Hey Everyone,

It’s time for us to do the next GDG Savannah event. A lot has happened in the time since our last meeting, including Bull Street labs relocating to a new location so keep an eye out for venue changes!

Now that we’re officially registered with Google’s developer group program we can pull from some of their content to share with the rest of the group.

There are some great workshops and tutorials in the GDG vaults and while I’d like to get some Tensor Flow workshops on the schedule I think this time we’ll take a bit of a detour and do a quick look at building native apps with Flutter!

I am still working out the date and venue but I’m hoping we can meet at The Creative Coast’s new office location on a Saturday this time to open it up to more people.

Feel free to message me any questions and keep an eye on Meetup in the next few days for a final date and location!

Looking forward to the next Meetup!
- Dustin

P.S. I am still looking for a co-organizer so we can hold these meetups more frequently. If anyone is interested or would like to “volunteer” a friend feel free to reach out to me at [masked].
events.how_to_find_us: Enter the Novel Coworking building, sign in at the security desk, then proceed to the 4th floor. The Creative Coast office is in the far back, left corner. We'll meet there.

upcoming.name: GDG Savannah Meetup
upcoming.description:
Hey Everyone,

It’s time for us to do the next GDG Savannah event.

This time we will finally dive into machine learning! Similar to the Flutter CodeLab we did last time, we'll run through an introductory TensorFlow CodeLab built with Python (https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/tensorflow-lab1-helloworld) in a CoLab session. If we have time after the introduction we'll also look at the follow-up session on computer vision (https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/tensorflow-lab2-computervision).

Finally, we will brainstorm some potential dates and themes for a mini conference called DevFest later this year.

Feel free to message me any questions and keep an eye on Meetup in the next couple of weeks for a final date and location!

Looking forward to the next Meetup!
- Dustin

P.S. I am still looking for a co-organizer so we can hold these meetups more frequently. If anyone is interested or would like to “volunteer” a friend feel free to reach out to me at [masked].
